<item>
            <title>[SPR-10382] Form tag prepending context/servlet path breaks use for portlets</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-10382</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the form tag for portlets, prepending the portlet&apos;s context is not wanted since we want the url to resolve to the portal&apos;s context and not the portlet&apos;s(where the form tag lives).  The portlet url tags generate portlet urls within the jsp like&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;/uPortal/f/s70/p/portlet-name/normal/action.uPpP_javax.portlet.action=saveItem&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
which resolve to /uPortal and not /PortletName&lt;/p&gt;

