                            <comment id="88776" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 15 Mar 2013 02:45:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-framework/commit/ad025b59c5e933fb7181c76f530e1f4ecc8f7c50&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;3.2.1 commit&lt;/a&gt; that introduced the change. We&apos;ll have it fixed in 3.2.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="89754" author="sindrit" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2013 07:36:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve managed to find a workaround for this by having the portal call WebUtils.exposeForwardRequestAttributes() before forwarding to the portlet application. This causes the form tag to use the portals context path instead of the portlet applications path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="90021" author="rstoya05-aop" created="Fri, 10 May 2013 09:56:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve reverted to the previous behavior of not prepending and added a new FormTag attribute called servletRelativeAction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
